# Next Client Warning Guards

Apply these checks whenever editing React components, especially files with `"use client"`.

## 1) Client component callback props (TS71007)

- In `"use client"` entry files, callback props must be named `action` or end with `Action`.
- Prefer `onOpenChangeAction`, `onSelectAction`, `onSaveAction`, etc.
- If a callback prop is only internal, move `"use client"` to a smaller leaf component instead of keeping it at a broader boundary.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
interface Props {
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
}

// ✅ GOOD
interface Props {
  onSelectAction: (id: string) => void;
}
```

## 2) Hook dependency hygiene (react-hooks/exhaustive-deps)

- Every value referenced inside `useEffect`/`useMemo`/`useCallback` must appear in dependencies.
- Do not place complex expressions directly in dependency arrays; extract them to named variables first.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
useEffect(() => sync(filtered), [items.filter((x) => x.visible)]);

// ✅ GOOD
const visibleItems = items.filter((x) => x.visible);
useEffect(() => sync(filtered), [filtered, visibleItems]);
```

## 3) Avoid raw `<img>` in Next.js (@next/next/no-img-element)

- Use `Image` from `next/image` for UI-rendered images.
- If you must use non-HTTP sources (for example `blob:` URLs), explain briefly in code and use an explicit lint-disable only at that line.
